The paper deals with the descriptional complexity of operations on semilinear sets, which are sets that can be expressed as a finite union of linear sets. This falls under the area of formal languages and automata theory, which is covered by cs.FL. The paper also involves the analysis of the maximal value and number of sets of periods and constants needed to describe a semilinear set, which relates to the study of data structures and algorithms, covered by cs.DS. The paper also involves the use of logic and set theory, which are covered by cs.LO. Additionally, the paper involves the use of computational complexity theory, which is covered by cs.CC, and information theory, which is covered by cs.IT.
